  "prompt": "What are good pranks at night?",
  "response": "Pranks can be a fun way to surprise your friends, but it's essential to consider the safety and feelings of those involved. Here are some light-hearted and harmless nighttime prank ideas:\n\n1. **Glow-in-the-Dark Stickers**: Place glow-in-the-dark stickers or shapes on a friend's ceiling. When they turn off the lights, they\u2019ll see an unexpected sight!\n\n2. **Fake Bug**: Use a realistic-looking fake insect (like a spider or cockroach) and place it near their bed or bathroom to create a startled reaction.\n\n3. **Saran Wrap on Doorway**: Stretch a sheet of Saran wrap across a doorway at face height. Make sure to do this safely to avoid injuries.\n\n4. **Air Horn Under the Chair**: Tape an air horn under a chair that will go off when someone sits down. Make sure it\u2019s a safe setup and people aren\u2019t in a position to get hurt.\n\n5. **Change Phone Alarm**: If you have access to a friend\u2019s phone, change their alarm tone to something silly or unexpected.\n\n6. **Lights Flickering**: If you have smart lights, program them to turn on and off sporadically while someone is in the room. This can create a spooky atmosphere!\n\n7. **Classic Ghost**: Use a white sheet to create a ghostly figure and place it in a visible spot or hang it in a way that it sways slightly with the breeze.\n\n8. **Plastic Wrap on Toilet Seat**: This classic trick works best in a bathroom and should be done with caution to avoid any mess or embarrassment.\n\n9. **Upside-Down Furniture**: If you\u2019re feeling ambitious and it's safe to do so, gently flip minor items of furniture upside down while your friends are asleep.\n\n10. **Mysterious Sounds**: Use a speaker to play unexpected sounds (like a door creaking or owl hooting) from a hidden location to create some mystery.\n\nAlways remember to consider the personalities of those being pranked and ensure that everyone has a good sense of humor about it. It\u2019s essential to keep pranks safe, respectful, and suitable for your audience.",
